A member of the SA National Defence Force (SANDF), arrested for illegal possession of ammunition, has been granted bail in the Phalaborwa Magistrates Court, Limpopo police said on Tuesday. The 40-year-old was arrested with a Senegalese national in Phalaborwa on Saturday. The SANDF member was spotted carrying a bag along Spekboom street in Phalaborwa. The police requested to search him, and during the search, 663 rounds of ammunition for a 7.63 rifle were found. The second man was nabbed on the same day at his house after 17 rounds of ammunition for a 9mm pistol were found in his possession, said police spokesperson Brigadier Motlafela Mojapelo. Both men have been charged with the illegal possession of ammunition. The SANDF member was granted bail of R1 000 while his co-accused was remanded in custody. Police investigations continued.